<path>pairing_logic_design.md</path>
<content>## Overview

The pairing logic is responsible for matching waiting nodes in a distributed system. It ensures every node eventually finds a partner while preventing deadlocks and handling failures gracefully.

## Pairing Process

- Generate candidate list from all waiting nodes
- Apply deterministic ordering based on consistent hashing of node IDs
- Select first available compatible pair from ordered list
- If no compatible pairs found, apply random shuffle and retry
- Mark paired nodes as unavailable to prevent duplicate pairing
- Remove successfully paired nodes from waiting pool

## Reliability Guarantees

- **Idempotent operations**: Each pairing request can be safely retried without side effects
- **Deadlock prevention**: Ordered selection and timeout-based retries eliminate circular waits
- **Failure handling**: Nodes removed from waiting pool after timeout if unresponsive
- **Consistent hashing**: Ensures deterministic pairing decisions across system
- **Eventual pairing**: All available nodes will eventually be paired given sufficient candidates
- **Node failure recovery**: Failed nodes automatically removed from consideration after health check timeout</content>
